### Install Fastify platform package with npm

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/performance.md

Command to install the required @nestjs/platform-fastify package for NestJS Fastify integration. This package provides the FastifyAdapter and related TypeScript types needed to configure Fastify as the HTTP provider.

```bash
npm i --save @nestjs/platform-fastify
```

--------------------------------

### Implement middleware with Fastify raw request/response objects

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/performance.md

TypeScript and JavaScript middleware implementation for NestJS with Fastify. Middleware functions receive raw req and res objects from Fastify instead of wrappers. The example shows a LoggerMiddleware class implementing NestMiddleware with proper type annotations for FastifyRequest and FastifyReply raw objects.

```typescript
import { Injectable, NestMiddleware } from '@nestjs/common';
import { FastifyRequest, FastifyReply } from 'fastify';

@Injectable()
export class LoggerMiddleware implements NestMiddleware {
  use(req: FastifyRequest['raw'], res: FastifyReply['raw'], next: () => void) {
    console.log('Request...');
    next();
  }
}
```

```javascript
import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';

@Injectable()
export class LoggerMiddleware {
  use(req, res, next) {
    console.log('Request...');
    next();
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Fastify to listen on all network interfaces

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/performance.md

TypeScript code showing how to configure Fastify to accept connections from all hosts by specifying '0.0.0.0' in the listen() method. By default, Fastify only listens on localhost (127.0.0.1), so this configuration is necessary for accepting external connections.

```typescript
async function bootstrap() {
  const app = await NestFactory.create<NestFastifyApplication>(
    AppModule,
    new FastifyAdapter(),
  );
  await app.listen(3000, '0.0.0.0');
}
```

