### NestJS End-to-End Testing with Fastify Adapter

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/fundamentals/unit-testing.md

Configure end-to-end testing for NestJS applications using Fastify as the HTTP adapter instead of Express. This example shows how to instantiate a NestFastifyApplication, initialize the Fastify adapter, use the inject method for HTTP simulation, and properly handle async operations with result validation and application cleanup.

```typescript
let app: NestFastifyApplication;

beforeAll(async () => {
  app = moduleRef.createNestApplication<NestFastifyApplication>(
    new FastifyAdapter(),
  );

  await app.init();
  await app.getHttpAdapter().getInstance().ready();
});

it(`/GET cats`, () => {
  return app
    .inject({
      method: 'GET',
      url: '/cats',
    })
    .then((result) => {
      expect(result.statusCode).toEqual(200);
      expect(result.payload).toEqual(/* expectedPayload */);
    });
});

afterAll(async () => {
  await app.close();
});
```

