### NestJS: Configure Fastify for Custom Query Parsing with `qs`

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/controllers.md

This example illustrates how to configure a NestJS application using the Fastify adapter to parse complex query parameters. It leverages the `querystringParser` option with the `qs` library to enable support for nested objects and arrays in query strings. The `qs` library needs to be installed separately.

```typescript
const app = await NestFactory.create<NestFastifyApplication>(
  AppModule,
  new FastifyAdapter({
    querystringParser: (str) => qs.parse(str),
  }),
);
```

