Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/faq/raw-body.md

This snippet demonstrates how to explicitly register a different body parser, such as 'text/plain', for a NestJS Fastify application. This allows the application to process content types beyond the default 'application/json' and 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' parsers, enhancing its flexibility in handling various request formats.

