### Configure Fastify Helmet CSP for GraphQL Playground in NestJS

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/security/helmet.md

Provides configurations for `@fastify/helmet` to resolve Content Security Policy (CSP) issues with GraphQL Playground when using `apollo-server-fastify` in NestJS applications on the Fastify platform. It includes directives for various content sources and an option to disable CSP entirely.

```typescript
await app.register(fastifyHelmet, {
   contentSecurityPolicy: {
     directives: {
       defaultSrc: [`'self'`, 'unpkg.com'],
       styleSrc: [
         `'self'`,
         `'unsafe-inline'`,
         'cdn.jsdelivr.net',
         'fonts.googleapis.com',
         'unpkg.com'
       ],
       fontSrc: [`'self'`, 'fonts.gstatic.com', 'data:'],
       imgSrc: [`'self'`, 'data:', 'cdn.jsdelivr.net'],
       scriptSrc: [
         `'self'`,
         `https: 'unsafe-inline'`,
         `cdn.jsdelivr.net`,
         `'unsafe-eval'`
       ]
     }
   }
 });

 // If you are not going to use CSP at all, you can use this:
 await app.register(fastifyHelmet, {
   contentSecurityPolicy: false
 });
```

