### Configure Fastify CORS with Custom Methods

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/migration.md

Enable additional HTTP methods (PUT, PATCH, DELETE) for CORS in NestJS Fastify adapter. By default, only CORS-safelisted methods are allowed. This example shows two approaches: passing the methods option to NestFactory.create or using the enableCors method after app creation.

```typescript
const methods = ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'PATCH', 'DELETE']; // OR comma-delimited string 'GET,POST,PUT,PATH,DELETE'

const app = await NestFactory.create<NestFastifyApplication>(
  AppModule,
  new FastifyAdapter(),
  { cors: { methods } },
);

// OR alternatively, you can use the `enableCors` method
const app = await NestFactory.create<NestFastifyApplication>(
  AppModule,
  new FastifyAdapter(),
);
app.enableCors({ methods });
```

