### Get Native HTTP Server Instance

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/faq/http-adapter.md

Access the native HTTP library instance (Express or Fastify) directly from the HTTP adapter. This allows you to use library-specific features not exposed through the NestJS adapter interface.

```APIDOC
## GET Native HTTP Server Instance

### Description
Retrieve the underlying native HTTP server library instance (Express or Fastify) from the adapter.

### Method
GET (synchronous retrieval)

### Usage
Call the `getInstance()` method on the httpAdapter object.

### Parameters
None

### Request Example
```typescript
const httpAdapter = app.getHttpAdapter();
const instance = httpAdapter.getInstance();
```

### Response
#### Success Response
- **instance** (Express | Fastify) - The native HTTP server library instance

#### Response Details
Returns either an Express application instance or a Fastify application instance, depending on the platform being used by the NestJS application.

### Notes
- Use this method to access platform-specific features
- The instance type depends on which HTTP adapter is configured (Express by default, Fastify optional)
- Allows direct interaction with the underlying HTTP server library
```

