### Injecting the HTTP Request object in NestJS

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/fundamentals/provider-scopes.md

To access the original HTTP request object within a request-scoped NestJS provider, inject the `REQUEST` token from `@nestjs/core`. This provider will automatically adopt a request scope, and the injected `request` property will hold the incoming Express or Fastify request object.

```typescript
import { Injectable, Scope, Inject } from '@nestjs/common';
import { REQUEST } from '@nestjs/core';
import { Request } from 'express';

@Injectable({ scope: Scope.REQUEST })
export class CatsService {
  constructor(@Inject(REQUEST) private request: Request) {}
}
```

