### Access Session Data via FastifyRequest Object in NestJS Route Handlers

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/sessions.md

This NestJS TypeScript example illustrates accessing and modifying session values directly through the `FastifyRequest` object within a route handler. It shows how to retrieve a session variable named 'visits', increment it, and then set the updated value back into the session.

```typescript
@Get()
findAll(@Req() request: FastifyRequest) {
  const visits = request.session.get('visits');
  request.session.set('visits', visits ? visits + 1 : 1);
}
```

