### Create Sequelize Database Provider with TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/recipes/sql-sequelize.md

Define a database provider that instantiates Sequelize with MySQL configuration, adds model definitions, and synchronizes database tables. This provider is exported as a custom NestJS provider for dependency injection across the application.

```typescript
import { Sequelize } from 'sequelize-typescript';
import { Cat } from '../cats/cat.entity';

export const databaseProviders = [
  {
    provide: 'SEQUELIZE',
    useFactory: async () => {
      const sequelize = new Sequelize({
