### Dynamically Render View in NestJS Controller using @Res

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/mvc.md

This TypeScript example shows how to dynamically render a template in a NestJS controller. By injecting the Express `response` object using `@Res()`, the controller can programmatically decide which template to render and pass data to it, offering more flexibility than the `@Render()` decorator.

```typescript
import { Get, Controller, Res, Render } from '@nestjs/common';
import { Response } from 'express';
import { AppService } from './app.service';

@Controller()
export class AppController {
  constructor(private appService: AppService) {}

  @Get()
  root(@Res() res: Response) {
